diff <- (trainset[grepl('V1_', colnames(trainset))] - trainset[grepl('V2_', colnames(trainset))])^2
colnames(diff) <- gsub('V1', 'DIFF', colnames(diff))
sqrt_diff <- sqrt(diff)
colnames(sqrt_diff) <- gsub('DIFF', 'SQRT', colnames(sqrt_diff))
log_diff <- log(diff)
colnames(log_diff) <- gsub('DIFF', 'LOG', colnames(log_diff))
trainset_ranger <- bind_cols(trainset, diff, log_diff, sqrt_diff)
library(ranger)
ranger_custom <- function(preds, data) {
  formula <- as.formula(sprintf('match ~ %s', paste(preds, collapse = ' + ')))
  ranger(formula, data=data, probability = TRUE)
}
preds_embeddings <- colnames(trainset_ranger)[grep('V1|V2', colnames(trainset_ranger))]
preds_diffs <- colnames(trainset_ranger)[grep('DIFF', colnames(trainset_ranger))]
preds_logdiffs <- colnames(trainset_ranger)[grep('LOG', colnames(trainset_ranger))]
preds_sqrtdiffs <- colnames(trainset_ranger)[grep('SQRT', colnames(trainset_ranger))]
trainset_predictions <- trainset_ranger %>%
  filter(set == 'train') %>%
  # sample_n(100) %>%
  modelr::crossv_kfold(10) %>%
  mutate(model_diffs = map(train, ~ranger_custom(preds_diffs, data=as.data.frame(.x))),
         model_logdiffs = map(train, ~ranger_custom(preds_logdiffs, data=as.data.frame(.x))),
         model_sqrtdiffs = map(train, ~ranger_custom(preds_sqrtdiffs, data=as.data.frame(.x))),
         model_diffs_sqrtdiffs = map(train, ~ranger_custom(c(preds_diffs, preds_sqrtdiffs), data=as.data.frame(.x))),
         model_all = map(train, ~ranger_custom(c(preds_diffs, preds_sqrtdiffs, preds_logdiffs, preds_embeddings), data=as.data.frame(.x)))) %>%
  gather(model, model_fit, starts_with('model')) %>%
  mutate(predictions = map2(model_fit, 
                            test, 
                            ~data.frame(match = as.data.frame(.y)$match, 
                                        score = predict(.x, data = as.data.frame(.y))$predictions[,2]))) %>%
  unnest(predictions)

Create prediction method

ranger:::predict.ranger

function (object, data = NULL, predict.all = FALSE, num.trees = object$num.trees, 
    type = "response", se.method = "infjack", quantiles = c(0.1, 
        0.5, 0.9), what = NULL, seed = NULL, num.threads = NULL, 
    verbose = TRUE, ...) 
{
    forest <- object$forest
    if (is.null(forest)) {
        stop("Error: No saved forest in ranger object. Please set write.forest to TRUE when calling ranger.")
    }
    if (object$importance.mode %in% c("impurity_corrected", "impurity_unbiased")) {
        warning("Forest was grown with 'impurity_corrected' variable importance. For prediction it is advised to grow another forest without this importance setting.")
    }
    if (type == "quantiles") {
        if (object$treetype != "Regression") {
            stop("Error: Quantile prediction implemented only for regression outcomes.")
        }
        if (is.null(object$random.node.values)) {
            stop("Error: Set quantreg=TRUE in ranger(...) for quantile prediction.")
        }
        if (is.null(data)) {
            if (is.null(object$random.node.values.oob)) {
                stop("Error: Set keep.inbag=TRUE in ranger(...) for out-of-bag quantile prediction or provide new data in predict(...).")
            }
            node.values <- object$random.node.values.oob
        }
        else {
            terminal.nodes <- predict(object, data, type = "terminalNodes")$predictions + 
                1
            node.values <- 0 * terminal.nodes
            for (tree in 1:num.trees) {
                node.values[, tree] <- object$random.node.values[terminal.nodes[, 
                  tree], tree]
            }
        }
        result <- list(num.samples = nrow(node.values), treetype = object$treetype, 
            num.independent.variables = object$num.independent.variables, 
            num.trees = num.trees)
        class(result) <- "ranger.prediction"
        if (is.null(what)) {
            result$predictions <- t(apply(node.values, 1, quantile, 
                quantiles, na.rm = TRUE))
            if (nrow(result$predictions) != result$num.samples) {
                result$predictions <- t(result$predictions)
            }
            colnames(result$predictions) <- paste("quantile=", 
                quantiles)
        }
        else {
            if (!is.function(what)) {
                stop("Error: Argument 'what' is not a function.")
            }
            result$predictions <- t(apply(node.values, 1, what))
        }
        result
    }
    else {
        if (is.null(data)) {
            stop("Error: Argument 'data' is required for non-quantile prediction.")
        }
        predict(forest, data, predict.all, num.trees, type, se.method, 
            seed, num.threads, verbose, object$inbag.counts, 
            ...)
    }
}
